<section class="content reveal">
  <h2>How It Started</h2>
  <p>
    UseJunior started on October 1, 2024, after Steven Obiajulu decided to leave his role at Ropes &amp; Gray
    to build useful tools for lawyers.
  </p>
  <p>
    Steven started coding at age 12, earned a mechanical engineering degree from MIT, and later practiced at Ropes &amp; Gray before starting UseJunior.
  </p>
  <p>
    In early customer work, one request kept repeating: editing existing Word documents safely was
    harder than generating new text. Teams needed precise changes inside real contracts, not generic
    document generation.
  </p>
  <p>
    We initially worked from python-docx conventions and wrote our own specs and Python implementations
    around the operations users requested most.
  </p>
  <p>
    We later ported our own Python implementation into our own TypeScript codebase so Safe DOCX could ship
    cleanly as a bundled MCP server, then improved incrementally as real-world bugs surfaced.
  </p>
  <p>
    Core implementation has been led by Steven, with input from a small engineering team, including his brother.
  </p>
</section>

